Security Controls & Architecture

Input validation: Prevents malicious input (XSS, injection) before processing

Sideloading: Installing apps outside official stores (security risk)

NAC (Network Access Control):

Enforces device compliance before network access

Can restrict or quarantine non-compliant devices

Application Allow List:

Only approved applications may run

Strong defense against malware

ğŸ§  Monitoring & Detection

EDR (Endpoint Detection & Response):

Monitors endpoints (PCs, phones, servers)

Detects malware, ransomware, suspicious behavior

IDS:

Network-based monitoring

Detects suspicious traffic but does NOT block

